						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the temple of Hanumān.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya: Rudradēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1169, Śaṅkarmaṇa,</hi> corresponding to 1247 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It registers gifts of land made by Bayyaladēvi, daughter of <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Rudradēva Mahārāju, to the temples of Tripurāntakadēva and Rāmanāthadēva of Nuduṟuṁpāḍu for the merit of herself, her daughter (name lost) and another named Kastūri.</p>						

						</summary>
